title: Star Wars airplane flies to Vancouver [Photos]
text:
Star Wars airplane flies to Vancouver First posted: Monday, October 19, 2015 11:14 AM EDT Star Wars plane Previous Next 
The All Nippon Airways (ANA) special plane painted like R2-D2 prepares to take off for a two-hour round trip at Haneda international airport in Tokyo, Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015. The Boeing 787 decorated with blue and silver pattern of R2-D2 will be be put on ANA's normal operation bound for Vancouver starting from Sunday. This is a part of ANA Star Wars project. The Japanese airline company announced earlier this year that it closed contract with Walt Disney Japan to use Star Wars characters until 2020. (AP Photo/Koji Sasahara) AP
